unque is a noun meaning "a hollow" in Qu: Image:Unque.gifUnque is also the name in Quenya of the sixteenth letter of the Tengwar alphabet. It is the fourth letter of the fourth grade or Tyellë
Note: which contains "voiced spirants" and it is the fourth letter in the fourth series of consonants. In the standard spelling of Quenya this letter represents NKW (or transcribed in English as NQU) while in Sindarin this letter represents GHW. In Westron the fourth series is used for the k-series
column4: and this letter represents GH. The Westron name for this letter is Agha.See Westron Tengwar

unque is a noun meaning "a hollow" in Qu: The word derives from the Primitive Quendian Sundocarme UNUK.
